sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: derived from bacteriaphage lambda operon. And placm, iLDH, patp2 are from the Registry. Beta-galactosidase coding sequence are reffered to pUC119 commerial vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is a lactic acid balance circuit in E.coli with lactose signal to initiate. And when the pH environment are within 7 to 9,the host strain will prepare beta-galactosidase for next lactose input.
